OL,3,C'No one is listening to us': Fear and
OL,4,Cfrustration as migration tensions grow
OL,6,FThis week, we went to the village of
OL,7,FStanwell, where a hotel continues to
OL,8,Fhouse single male asylum seekers
OL,9,Fdespite the protests, over a hundred
OL,10,Fconsecutive nights, of local people.
OL,12,FWhat was noticeable was the number of
OL,13,Fchildren on the march.
OL,15,F"It really makes me scared because my
OL,16,Fmum tells me I'm not allowed to walk
OL,17,Fon the streets any more because of the
OL,18,Fmen in there," one girl told ITV News.
